# Scripts that are executed inside Linux containers (the patched-Javy plugin
# build in plugin/javy-toolchain/) must keep LF endings in the WORKING TREE, not
# just in the object store. With core.autocrlf=true on Windows they otherwise
# check out CRLF and the container's bash fails on `set -euo pipefail\r` with
# "set: pipefail: invalid option name", making the documented Docker build
# recipe impossible to run from a Windows checkout.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf

# The vendored Javy plugin artifact is binary; never touch its bytes.
*.wasm binary
